      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Bernice W. Ames was an American poet.  Her work appeared in <emph render="italic">Midwest Quarterly</emph>, <emph render="italic">University Review</emph>, <emph render="italic">Yankee</emph>, <emph render="italic">Christian Science Monitor</emph>, and in many other publications. She was a member of the Poetry Society of America, and its Bernice W. Ames Award is named for her.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Bernice W. Ames Papers</emph> consists of correspondence, manuscripts, memorabilia, and printed material.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
